NAIROBI, KENYA: KCB Group has re-appointed Chief Executive Officer Joshua Oigara for a new four-year term, Kenya’s biggest bank by assets said. In a report seen by Reuters on Wednesday, the bank said Oigara’s appointment was effective from January 1. He was first appointed to the position in January 2013. ALSO READ:

KCB sends home 709 amid rising employee costs The bank, which also operates in neighbouring Uganda, Tanzania, Rwanda, Burundi and South Sudan, posted a flat 2017 pretax profit of Sh29.1 billion after achieving 10 percent growth the previous year.